(
<figureCitation id="EA9B2A14A359B03EFF34ECAD8D1B65A8" box="[159,293,1170,1196]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–16" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1232,1256]" captionTargetBox="[192,1376,204,1211]" captionTargetId="figure-196@3.[167,1405,179,1223]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 10–16. Scaphoideus species. 10–12, S. rubroguttatus, 10–11, aedeagus (left lateral and posterior, respectively), 12, style; 13–14, S. unimaculata, aedeagus (left lateral and posterior, respectively). 15–16, S. quangtriensis, aedeagus, left lateral and posterior view, respectively)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5077420" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5077420/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Figs 13, 14</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="EA9B2A14A359B03EFE99ECAD8D6E65A8" box="[306,336,1170,1196]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–22" captionStartId="4.[151,269,1907,1931]" captionTargetBox="[188,1384,202,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-56@4.[152,1435,157,1881]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 17–22. Scaphoideus species (habitus). 17, S. unimaculatus (holotype); 18, S. quangtriensis (holotype); 19, S. rubroguttatus; 20, S. dellagiustinai (paratype, France); 21, S. baeiticus (holotype); 22, S. albosignatus (syntype)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5077422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5077422/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">17</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="721F3691A359B03EFF3CECDD8FDF65F8" blockId="2.[151,1436,1250,1962]" box="[151,993,1250,1276]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">
Length: 
<specimenCount id="64A6FD18A359B03EFEAAECDD8D2B65F2" box="[257,277,1250,1270]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
, 4.7–4.9 mm (x 
<specimenCount id="64A6FD18A359B03EFE7BECDD8E5B65F8" box="[464,613,1250,1276]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" type="generic">3 specimens</specimenCount>
); 
<specimenCount id="64A6FD18A359B03EFDD2ECDD8EB365F2" box="[633,653,1250,1270]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
, 5.0–5.2 mm (x 
<specimenCount id="64A6FD18A359B03EFCECECDD8FE765F8" box="[839,985,1250,1276]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" type="generic">2 specimens</specimenCount>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="721F3691A359B03EFF11ED358D6B6470" blockId="2.[151,1436,1250,1962]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Yellow marked with orange on vertex and disc of pronotum and scutellum; two incomplete transverse narrow bands on face dorsally coalescing to form a diamond-shaped mark. Forewing with a small brown spot in third apical cell.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="721F3691A359B03EFF64EDBB89B164EB" blockId="2.[151,1436,1250,1962]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">
External features as in 
<taxonomicName id="B5A04D12A359B03EFE4DEDBB8E996499" authorityName="Webb &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2007" box="[486,679,1412,1438]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dellagiustinai">
<emphasis id="40D4EA83A359B03EFE4DEDBB8DCB6499" box="[486,501,1412,1437]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="40D4EA83A359B03EFDADEDBB8E996499" box="[518,679,1412,1437]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">dellagiustinai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="EA9B2A14A359B03EFD11EDBB8F19649A" box="[698,807,1412,1438]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1889,1913]" captionTargetBox="[162,1413,699,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-107@1.[144,1461,632,1899]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Scaphoideus dellagiustinai, 1, 2, head and thorax (dorsal and lateral view, respectively); 3, face; 4, style; 5, connective; 6, 7 aedeagus (left lateral and posterior view, respectively); 8, male genital capsule; 9, valve, subgenital plates (ventral left, dorsal right) and style." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5077416" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5077416/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Figs 1–3</figureCitation>
). Head relatively narrow in dorsal view with vertex slightly longer than basal width; fore margin of the head truncate in lateral view; clypeus narrow dorsally and antennae situated relatively high on face. Forewing with two recurved costal veins from outer subapical cell.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="721F3691A359B03EFF68EDC28D08665D" blockId="2.[151,1436,1250,1962]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">
Male pygofer, subgenital plate and connective as in 
<taxonomicName id="B5A04D12A359B03EFC9BEDC28FCE6712" authorityName="Webb &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2007" box="[816,1008,1533,1559]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dellagiustinai">
<emphasis id="40D4EA83A359B03EFC9BEDC28F006712" box="[816,830,1533,1558]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="40D4EA83A359B03EFCE4EDC28FCE6712" box="[847,1008,1533,1558]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">dellagiustinai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="EA9B2A14A359B03EFBAAEDC288B26713" box="[1025,1164,1533,1559]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1889,1913]" captionTargetBox="[162,1413,699,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-107@1.[144,1461,632,1899]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Scaphoideus dellagiustinai, 1, 2, head and thorax (dorsal and lateral view, respectively); 3, face; 4, style; 5, connective; 6, 7 aedeagus (left lateral and posterior view, respectively); 8, male genital capsule; 9, valve, subgenital plates (ventral left, dorsal right) and style." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5077416" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5077416/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Figs 5, 8, 9</figureCitation>
): pygofer without processes, broadly rounded apically in lateral view with a group of very long setae apically and a few shorter setae subapically. Subgenital plate distinctly shorter than pygofer, broad basally with distal two thirds very narrow in ventral view; a uniseriate row of macrosetae subbasally and a few short fine setae distally. Connective with a pair of slender paraphyses, each paraphysis tapering distally. Style as in 
<taxonomicName id="B5A04D12A359B03EFBC2EEA2891867B2" authorityName="Matsumura, Nusillard" authorityYear="2007" box="[1129,1318,1693,1719]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubroguttatus">
<emphasis id="40D4EA83A359B03EFBC2EEA2884667B2" box="[1129,1144,1693,1718]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="40D4EA83A359B03EFB2DEEA2891867B2" box="[1158,1318,1693,1718]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">rubroguttatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="EA9B2A14A359B03EFA9CEEA289B067B3" box="[1335,1422,1693,1719]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–16" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1232,1256]" captionTargetBox="[192,1376,204,1211]" captionTargetId="figure-196@3.[167,1405,179,1223]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 10–16. Scaphoideus species. 10–12, S. rubroguttatus, 10–11, aedeagus (left lateral and posterior, respectively), 12, style; 13–14, S. unimaculata, aedeagus (left lateral and posterior, respectively). 15–16, S. quangtriensis, aedeagus, left lateral and posterior view, respectively)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5077420" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5077420/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus disassociated from connective; shaft elongate, as long as basal apodeme, with a pair of elongate apical processes and a dorsal serrated flange basally on each side, gonopore apical on posterior surface; basal apodeme compressed anteroposteriorly, bifurcate apically and produced into a lobe on each side at midlength (
<figureCitation id="EA9B2A14A359B03EFF34EF008D16665D" box="[159,296,1853,1881]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–16" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1232,1256]" captionTargetBox="[192,1376,204,1211]" captionTargetId="figure-196@3.[167,1405,179,1223]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 10–16. Scaphoideus species. 10–12, S. rubroguttatus, 10–11, aedeagus (left lateral and posterior, respectively), 12, style; 13–14, S. unimaculata, aedeagus (left lateral and posterior, respectively). 15–16, S. quangtriensis, aedeagus, left lateral and posterior view, respectively)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5077420" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5077420/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Figs 13–14</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="721F3691A359B03EFF6EEF5789A966AE" blockId="2.[151,1436,1250,1962]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Female pygofer in lateral view with tufts of very long macrosetae apically, shorter setae centrally and a uniseriate row subbasally adjacent to valvulae; pregenital sternite with posterior margin more or less straight.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="26DF6619A358B03FFF3CECEF8EE26428" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5077420" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5077420" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5077420/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" startId="3.[151,269,1232,1256]" targetBox="[192,1376,204,1211]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="721F3691A358B03FFF3CECEF8EE26428" blockId="3.[151,1436,1232,1324]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="40D4EA83A358B03FFF3CECEF8D5F65EC" bold="true" box="[151,353,1232,1256]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">FIGURES 10–16.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="B5A04D12A358B03FFEC0ECEE8E6E65E3" box="[363,592,1232,1256]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="40D4EA83A358B03FFEC0ECEE8DCC65EC" box="[363,498,1233,1256]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Scaphoideus</emphasis>
species.
</taxonomicName>
10–12, 
<taxonomicName id="B5A04D12A358B03FFD06ECEE8F6265EC" authorityName="Matsumura, Nusillard" authorityYear="2007" box="[685,860,1232,1256]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubroguttatus">
<emphasis id="40D4EA83A358B03FFD06ECEE8E8465EC" box="[685,698,1233,1256]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="40D4EA83A358B03FFD60ECEE8F6265EC" box="[715,860,1233,1256]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">rubroguttatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 10–11, aedeagus (left lateral and posterior, respectively), 12, style; 13–14, 
<taxonomicName id="B5A04D12A358B03FFE1AECCC8E6B640E" box="[433,597,1267,1290]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unimaculata">
<emphasis id="40D4EA83A358B03FFE1AECCC8D80640E" box="[433,446,1267,1290]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="40D4EA83A358B03FFE7BECCC8E6B640E" box="[464,597,1267,1290]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">unimaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, aedeagus (left lateral and posterior, respectively). 15–16, 
<taxonomicName id="B5A04D12A358B03FFB4FECCC89AB640E" authorityName="Webb &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2007" box="[1252,1429,1267,1290]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quangtriensis">
S. 
<emphasis id="40D4EA83A358B03FFAAFECCC89AB640E" box="[1284,1429,1267,1290]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">quangtriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, aedeagus, left lateral and posterior view, respectively).
</paragraph>
</caption>
