<subSubSection id="3ABA651AA358B03FFF6DEE3F88886746" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="721F3691A358B03FFF6DEE3F88886746" blockId="3.[151,1436,1416,1602]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="40D4EA83A358B03FFF6DEE3F8D01671E" bold="true" box="[198,319,1536,1562]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="B5A04D12A358B03FFDC6EE3E8F15671E" authorityName="Webb &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2007" box="[621,811,1536,1562]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dellagiustinai">
<emphasis id="40D4EA83A358B03FFDC6EE3E8E42671E" box="[621,636,1537,1562]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="40D4EA83A358B03FFD21EE3E8F15671E" box="[650,811,1537,1562]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">dellagiustinai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="B5A04D12A358B03FFC92EE3E8FC8671E" authorityName="Matsumura, Nusillard" authorityYear="2007" box="[825,1014,1536,1562]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubroguttatus">
<emphasis id="40D4EA83A358B03FFC92EE3E8F76671E" box="[825,840,1537,1562]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="40D4EA83A358B03FFCFDEE3E8FC8671E" box="[854,1014,1537,1562]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">rubroguttatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="B5A04D12A358B03FFB85EE3E88D4671E" authorityName="Webb &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2007" box="[1070,1258,1536,1562]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quangtriensis">
<emphasis id="40D4EA83A358B03FFB85EE3E8802671E" box="[1070,1084,1537,1562]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="40D4EA83A358B03FFBE0EE3E88D4671E" box="[1099,1258,1537,1562]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">quangtriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but can be distinguished by the dark mark dorsally on the face and the longer apical aedeagal processes.
</paragraph>
